flowRoot.flowPara: The panel primarily deals with URI access.

URI handlers that are setup by default don't need any kind of approval from the user - they open the relevant link when it's clicked without any additional interaction being required. This includes web, mail, calendar, maps.

If a link is opened that hasn't been setup by default, the user has to select an application to open it with, using the app chooser dialog. This grants the selected app permission to access the relevant URI scheme, and the URI scheme and app is added to the "additional link types" section of the settings panel.

URI schemes that have been approved can be revoked by clicking the X button. This allows a different application to be set as the default handler, by selected it from the app chooser dialog the next time a link with that scheme is opened.
Apps that appear in the list open files/links without the need to go through the app chooser dialog.
The first list is static. Apps can be changed.
The second set is dynamic - grows as file types and apps are used. Mappings can only be removed.

flowRoot.flowPara: File types: panel allows selecting the default mimetype handler for music, video and photos. For each of these, a dropdown is available if there is an application capable of handling the mimetype (otherwise, the row reads "No default application available").
